Create an Enhanced Bot from Scratch or from a Template

Use the guided setup to create an enhanced bot from scratch or from a template. The guided setup is fitted with tools that help create exceptional bot experiences, including helpful custom and system dialogs, entities and variables for capturing customer input, plus bot analytics.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
To use enhanced Messaging channels with Enhanced Bots, view required editions.


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:	
Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots


Launch the guided setup from the Einstein Bots main page. For your first bot, click Create a New Bot. Otherwise, click New.
Select Enhanced Bot, and then click Next.
To create an enhanced bot from scratch, select Start from Scratch. To create an enhanced bot from a template, select a bot template.


When you complete the guided setup, the system creates the bot and enters the Bot Builder Dialog page.

CONFIGURE ROUTING FOR YOUR BOT
INBOUND: SEND CONVERSATIONS TO YOUR ENHANCED BOT	OUTBOUND: TRANSFER CONVERSATIONS FROM YOUR ENHANCED BOT


In the guided setup, you can choose to create a simple inbound Omni-Channel flow. You can also create or select a default outbound Omni-Channel flow.


Any Omni-Channel flow that Salesforce creates doesnâ€™t route conversations to or from your bot until you customize and activate it in Flow Builder.
title: Creating an Enhanced Service Cloud Bot
